<subSubSection pageNumber="904" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="904">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="904">Note:</emphasis>
Lewis (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="904">J. S. African Bot.</emphasis>
7: 59. 1941) formally chose the Breyn plate as the type, accepted it as belonging to what had been known as 
<taxonomicName authority="(Thunb.) Vent." authorityName="Vent." baseAuthorityName="Thunb." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Iridaceae" genus="Homeria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="collina">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="904">Homeria collina</emphasis>
(Thunb.) Vent.
</taxonomicName>
, and made the combination 
<taxonomicName authority="(L.) G. J. Lewis" authorityName="G. J. Lewis" authorityYear="1941" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1753" class="Liliopsida" family="Iridaceae" genus="Homeria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="breyniana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="904">H. breyniana</emphasis>
(L.) G.J. Lewis
</taxonomicName>
for it. However, other authors, notably Goldblatt (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="904">J. S. African Bot.</emphasis>
39: 139, f. 2. 1982), have been less certain of the identity of the type and appear to have informally rejected the name in favour of 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="904">
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Liliopsida" family="Iridaceae" genus="Homeria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="collina">H. collina</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
